caption:
Azalea City Gym Leader Bugsy;  “The Walking Bug Pokémon Encyclopedia”

Second Johto Gym and… it’s just ok… in Gen II at least. Gen IV once again steps up to the plate and re-works the gym into actual bug habitat (while in the past it just looked like a garden). As for the fight, it’s pretty simple till he bust out his Scyther (another Gen I pokemon as an ace?) and cuts down your team.

When it came to this picture, I was thinking about giving him a Ledian or Ariados (the latter especially to match the gym’s Gen IV version) but it felt right to just evolve his Scyther in Scizor.

blog.name: askspringbringers
blog.title: Children of the Cherry Blossom
blog.description:
"WELCOME TO THE GARDEN!"

~ Pokeask Blog featuring a Shaymin and Lopunny who bring about the seasons ~

Asks in Inbox: 6 [ open ]

summary: Leilani looks around joyfully at the garden: the fluttering cherry blossoms, the pond teeming with koi, the towering bamboo...
question: Leilani looks around joyfully at the garden: the fluttering cherry blossoms, the pond teeming with koi, the towering bamboo shoots. She was fascinated by it all. She looked up when she heard the Shaymin and Lopunny speak. "Oh. I'm sorry. I was just passing through, because I'm looking for... someone. This place looked really pretty, so I thought I would take a look at it! Where is this anyway? I bet it took lots of work to make it look this beautiful!"
answer:
“You guys have come a really long way to not know where you are!” Crylic said aloud, their voice gentle and calm as they watched the koifish.

“But it’s okay! I’ll show you!”

“See, we live in this place called Feikyou! It translates to ‘Unwilting Meadow.’ It’s green almost everywhere here! There’s the kingdom of Ii’xua, Midorinaka, Edena, Eternitia, Igarashi, Katako, and Memori!”

“And we are….”

“Right here in Tataki Village. Right in the middle of Midorinaka.”

> ASK HINTS HAVE BEEN ADDED.

[ @leilani-popplio | @fairy-dreadnaught ]

title: Rhyhorn - 111

Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokemon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.

- Pokemon Ruby, Omega Ruby
